- What?
- You’re good at singing.

514
00:53:14,097 --> 00:53:15,810
- What are you talking about?
- I heard you sing before.

515
00:53:15,807 --> 00:53:16,930
- I can’t sing.
- I’ll go then.

516
00:53:16,927 --> 00:53:20,237
- ‘I’m a local girl from Chiangmai…’
-Excuse me? My friend wants to join you.

517
00:53:20,237 --> 00:53:21,583
Come on up here.

518
00:53:21,607 --> 00:53:23,983
- Go, Phaya. / - Yeah.

519
00:53:25,050 --> 00:53:26,197
Are you chicken out?

520
00:53:27,497 --> 00:53:31,130
That’s my boy. Just a swig to boost up your guts.

521
00:53:31,357 --> 00:53:36,017
- I’ll show you.
- Yeah, that’s my friend, everyone.

522
00:53:39,903 --> 00:53:41,450
Do you need anything, I’ll go get it for you.

523
00:53:41,450 --> 00:53:45,257
- Mine is done. Get me one of this.
- Me too. I’ll have one too.

524
00:53:45,677 --> 00:53:48,570
Make it five, Tharn. Five bottles of beer.

525
00:53:55,237 --> 00:53:58,903
(Music)

526
00:55:23,687 --> 00:55:26,103
Let’s play some game.

527
00:55:26,097 --> 00:55:27,090
What game?

528
00:55:27,087 --> 00:55:28,623
Spin The Bottle game.

529
00:55:28,617 --> 00:55:32,263
- Let’s clear the table.
- Okay

530
00:55:32,257 --> 00:55:35,370
- But I’m going to alter the rule a bit.
- How?

531
00:55:35,370 --> 00:55:40,657
If the bottle points toward anyone, that person can ask anyone a question.

532
00:55:42,137 --> 00:55:43,183
- Okay
- Let’s do that.

533
00:55:43,177 --> 00:55:47,703
If the you couldn’t answer the question, you must down the glass.

534
00:55:54,657 --> 00:55:56,957
- We’ll surely get drunk.
- Who’s it?

535
00:55:57,330 --> 00:55:59,517
- Who’s it?
- What the fuck are you doing, Yai?

536
00:56:00,143 --> 00:56:02,943
Don’t worry, my bro. I’ll take care of it.

537
00:56:02,937 --> 00:56:05,303
- Come on
- Bring it on.

538
00:56:05,303 --> 00:56:07,857
- Let’s start.
- Who’s first?

539
00:56:09,297 --> 00:56:11,330
It’s me.

540
00:56:11,327 --> 00:56:12,423
Go on then.

541
00:56:12,417 --> 00:56:13,463
Whom do you want to ask?

542
00:56:13,757 --> 00:56:17,463
I’m going to ask Tharn.

543
00:56:20,890 --> 00:56:21,903
Go on.

544
00:56:22,487 --> 00:56:26,463
Do you have anyone you like right now?

545
00:56:29,517 --> 00:56:34,450
Answer, answer, answer!

546
00:56:34,737 --> 00:56:38,743
- Booo.
- What a waste.

547
00:56:44,857 --> 00:56:45,730
I’ll ask Tharn.

548
00:56:47,397 --> 00:56:48,783
It has to be like this, bro.

549
00:56:48,777 --> 00:56:49,757
Here we go.

550
00:56:49,757 --> 00:56:50,530
Again?

551
00:56:50,527 --> 00:56:51,677
Go on.

552
00:56:51,677 --> 00:56:57,730
What’s your type? Is it someone around here?

553
00:56:58,050 --> 00:57:04,097
Answer, answer, answer!

554
00:57:04,687 --> 00:57:08,210
Geez.

555
00:57:09,077 --> 00:57:11,130
You!

556
00:57:11,903 --> 00:57:13,297
I’ll ask Tharn.

557
00:57:14,157 --> 00:57:16,530
Hold on. That’s enough.

558
00:57:16,527 --> 00:57:18,290
Easy there.

559
00:57:18,287 --> 00:57:21,170
Let’s stop. Look at him, he’s all red.

560
00:57:21,167 --> 00:57:23,823
Fine, I won’t ask him then.

561
00:57:24,177 --> 00:57:26,277
- I’ll ask you instead.
- Oh, it’s your turn now.

562
00:57:26,277 --> 00:57:27,743
Just sit down.

563
00:57:28,863 --> 00:57:30,687
Listen.

564
00:57:30,687 --> 00:57:33,757
If you can pick anyone in this table to go home with you,

565
00:57:34,437 --> 00:57:37,703
whom will you choose?

566
00:57:39,143 --> 00:57:40,543
Answer it.

567
00:57:40,543 --> 00:57:44,497
Answer, answer, answer!

568
00:58:19,657 --> 00:58:22,037
- I’m going to choose…
- Yes?

569
00:58:29,297 --> 00:58:32,957
- Shit!
- Oh, shit!

570
00:58:32,957 --> 00:58:33,850
Tharn!

571
00:58:34,583 --> 00:58:37,177
Tharn! Are you okay?

572
00:58:38,143 --> 00:58:39,690
We shouldn’t have picked on him.

573
00:58:40,263 --> 00:58:41,530
Tharn, are you all right?

574
00:58:41,877 --> 00:58:43,703
I’ll take him to wash up first.

575
00:58:43,903 --> 00:58:45,517
No more drinking, okay?

576
00:58:45,837 --> 00:58:47,050
Let’s go.

577
00:58:47,377 --> 00:58:50,290
Geez. I was afraid he’d puke all over me.

578
00:58:50,423 --> 00:58:52,543
Are they actually….?

579
00:58:54,850 --> 00:58:57,570
Are you okay?

580
00:59:00,730 --> 00:59:01,757
Wash your face first.

581
00:59:11,277 --> 00:59:12,330
Geez.

582
00:59:13,383 --> 00:59:15,063
Sit down. Sit.

583
00:59:15,423 --> 00:59:16,410
Already.

584
00:59:17,823 --> 00:59:19,583
- Hey.
- Huh?

585
00:59:20,663 --> 00:59:22,783
- Are you okay?
- Yeahh.

586
00:59:24,810 --> 00:59:26,423
If you want to feel better,

587
00:59:27,477 --> 00:59:28,397
I have this.

588
00:59:28,927 --> 00:59:29,957
It’d help.

589
00:59:31,967 --> 00:59:33,417
I’ll make it for you.

590
00:59:33,597 --> 00:59:34,557
Just stay still.

591
00:59:35,503 --> 00:59:36,423
Don’t move.

592
00:59:43,957 --> 00:59:44,850
Open your mouth.

593
00:59:44,970 --> 00:59:45,757
Drink it

594
00:59:53,103 --> 00:59:57,103
- Feel better?
- Umm, yeah.

595
00:59:58,317 --> 01:00:00,037
Very good.

596
01:00:00,037 --> 01:00:05,257
- Let’s freshen you up a bit.
- Geez, what’s wrong with you?

597
01:00:05,823 --> 01:00:06,677
Take this.

598
01:00:06,703 --> 01:00:09,197
You really like for bugging me.

599
01:00:12,247 --> 01:00:14,530
- Get off me.
- No.

600
01:00:15,690 --> 01:00:19,863
I’m not going to let you go. I’ll hold on to you tight.

601
01:00:20,223 --> 01:00:23,743
You, evil jellyfish.

602
01:00:26,317 --> 01:00:31,047
Are you sure? This jellyfish’s sting is very painful.

603
01:00:31,837 --> 01:00:33,797
It will go directly to your heart.

604
01:00:35,930 --> 01:00:40,023
The heart, the heart, the heart.

605
01:00:40,023 --> 01:00:43,577
Stop it.  You’re like a baby when you’re drunk.

606
01:00:46,343 --> 01:00:47,717
Let me return the favor.

607
01:01:17,917 --> 01:01:19,010
What’s wrong?

608
01:01:21,663 --> 01:01:23,277
Where did you get this necklace from?

609
01:01:27,757 --> 01:01:28,903
This amulet?

610
01:01:30,210 --> 01:01:32,130
It’s the same.

611
01:01:33,690 --> 01:01:34,687
Same as what?

612
01:01:36,663 --> 01:01:41,717
Same as the amulet that I used to give to a boy.

613
01:01:44,377 --> 01:01:46,397
You used to give a boy an amulet like this?

614
01:01:47,357 --> 01:01:48,477
Yeah.

615
01:01:50,983 --> 01:01:52,650
When? Where?

616
01:01:53,090 --> 01:01:54,223
Tell me more about it.

617
01:01:54,217 --> 01:01:56,263
It was when…

618
01:01:56,930 --> 01:01:57,783
Yes?

619
01:01:57,970 --> 01:02:01,103
When…

620
01:02:01,183 --> 01:02:04,717
Hey, wake up. Talk to me first.

621
01:02:08,743 --> 01:02:10,423
Geez, Tharn.

622
01:02:13,330 --> 01:02:14,037
Sit down first.

623
01:02:15,137 --> 01:02:19,383
- Wake up. Tell me where was it?
- It was…

624
01:02:19,657 --> 01:02:20,570
Tharn.

625
01:02:20,930 --> 01:02:21,797
Tharn.

626
01:02:22,397 --> 01:02:23,290
Tharn.

627
01:02:24,183 --> 01:02:25,527
Talk to me first.

628
01:02:25,527 --> 01:02:28,143
Shit! I’m sorry.

629
01:02:28,137 --> 01:02:31,903
Wait! It’s not what you think.

630
01:02:32,143 --> 01:02:35,930
It’s good that you’re here. He’s already passed out. What to do now?

631
01:02:36,850 --> 01:02:41,250
I thought so. He drank a gallon of it.

632
01:02:42,463 --> 01:02:43,703
Now, what?

633
01:02:44,850 --> 01:02:46,837
Okay, I know what to do.

634
01:02:48,530 --> 01:02:51,810
You go and drop him off at his condo.

635
01:02:52,247 --> 01:02:55,583
But I’m drunk too. I can’t do that.

636
01:02:55,583 --> 01:02:58,217
So am I. I’m going to call a cab for you.

637
01:02:58,477 --> 01:02:59,237
Come here.

638
01:03:00,770 --> 01:03:03,983
- Sit down.
- What the heck are you doing?

639
01:03:03,977 --> 01:03:06,437
Ouch!

640
01:03:08,617 --> 01:03:11,877
- Geez, he’s heavy.
- Yai!

641
01:03:12,290 --> 01:03:15,703
- Hang on.
- Now, go.

642
01:03:15,957 --> 01:03:16,583
Where?

643
01:03:16,583 --> 01:03:19,657
Wait for me in front of the club.  I’ll let you know when the cab is here.

644
01:03:25,597 --> 01:03:32,063
Tharn, my bro. I’ve done everything I could for you.

645
01:03:34,677 --> 01:03:36,930
Geez, what’s wrong with him?

646
01:03:38,423 --> 01:03:40,210
Where are you taking me?

647
01:03:40,343 --> 01:03:41,717
Your place.

648
01:03:42,290 --> 01:03:45,023
Go back and get Yai too.

649
01:03:45,343 --> 01:03:47,157
I don’t want to sleep alone.

650
01:03:47,663 --> 01:03:49,183
I’ll stay with you.

651
01:03:52,250 --> 01:03:54,543
But first, get off me.

652
01:03:55,423 --> 01:03:56,263
Where’s the cab?

653
01:03:57,143 --> 01:03:59,050
Just wait here.

654
01:04:01,370 --> 01:04:02,210
Sorry

655
01:04:02,543 --> 01:04:03,437
Just wait here.

656
01:04:08,397 --> 01:04:11,010
Shit, whose car is it?

657
01:04:19,597 --> 01:04:22,050
- Dr. Chalothorn.
- Tharn.

658
01:04:23,650 --> 01:04:24,537
Excuse me?

659
01:04:46,277 --> 01:04:50,223
Tharn and I have known Dr. Chalothorn since we were young.

660
01:04:50,497 --> 01:04:54,237
Good for him.  Now, he’d someone to take care of him when he’s drunk.

661
01:04:56,537 --> 01:05:02,623
Grandma, maybe it’s time for me to find out…

662
01:05:02,650 --> 01:05:05,217
what those dreams actually mean.

663
01:05:05,517 --> 01:05:09,677
I’m going to start from where it begins – where all those dreams started.

664
01:05:09,677 --> 01:05:11,037
Phaya.

665
01:05:12,327 --> 01:05:15,503
Tharn.  Why are you here?

666
01:06:36,017 --> 01:06:42,177
The Sign
